# Firewall Configuration

## Overview
Configured a host-based firewall on a Linux VM using UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall).
The goal was to establish a baseline security policy by defining rules for 
allowed and denied traffic based on real-world best practices.

## Tools Used
- UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall)
- Ubuntu 26.04 (ARM) running in UTM on macOS
- Linux terminal

## What I Did
- Set default policy to deny all incoming traffic and allow all outgoing traffic
- Allowed SSH (port 22) to maintain remote management access
- Allowed HTTP (port 80) and HTTPS (port 443) for web traffic
- Explicitly blocked Telnet (port 23) due to its lack of encryption
- Verified ruleset using `ufw status verbose` and saved output for documentation


## Skills Demonstrated
- Linux firewall configuration with UFW
- Understanding of common ports and protocols
- Default deny security policy implementation
- Documenting security decisions with clear reasoning
